{"key":"processedPost-15700906","value":{"id":15700906,"first":15700296,"last":15700906,"when":1327245071,"utime":"01/22/12 05:11 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>gratefulskinny said:</b><br /><br />Why is it best to have an even pinse<br /></blockquote><br /><br />It's best to have an even pinset because it shows you've learned to juggle all the growth and fruiting parameters, thus giving maximum yield.<br /><br /><blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>gratefulskinny said:</b>why do people pick all of their mushrooms at once?<br /></blockquote><br /><br />Because they're either lazy or inexperienced.&nbsp; Pick the fruits over the course of a few days as they're ready, which means shortly before the veil tears.&nbsp; Those who wait until they have flat caps puking spores everywhere pick all at once, but get very poor quality.&nbsp; Food quality is far better in the large pin stage before the veil begins to tear, so pick then if you're eating them.&nbsp; If you're making prints, allow a couple to open up.<br />RR","title":"Re: why an even pinset/why harvest at once","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}